{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QFaybtmKDhXYP4ZWJKfXVH","type":"tool_result","content":"375\t10a commit range: `c7c51f1..12faeaf` (8 commits).\n376\t\n377\t### Phase 10b — Build remaining engine seams + complete CLI coverage\n378\t\n379\tEngine seams to build in 10b. Output shapes are already specified in\n380\t`design/recovery.md` lines 73–77; this slice implements them and re-exports\n381\tthe corresponding reporting types per the same facade rule.\n382\t\n383\t| Seam method                      | Output type              | Spec status / build risk                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |\n384\t| -------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n385\t| `Engine::verify_embedder(...)`   | `VerifyEmbedderReport`   | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:73`). Reads stored embedder identity (already persisted per AC-048/048b) + compares to supplied. Low build risk.                                                                                                                 |\n386\t| `Engine::dump_schema()`          | `DumpSchemaReport`       | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:75`). SQLite introspection (`user_version`, `sqlite_schema` walk). Low build risk.                                                                                                                                               |\n387\t| `Engine::dump_row_counts()`      | `DumpRowCountsReport`    | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:76`). Canonical table row counts. Low build risk.                                                                                                                                                                                |\n388\t| `Engine::dump_profile()`         | `DumpProfileReport`      | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:77`). Reads stored embedder identity / vectorized kinds. Low build risk.                                                                                                                                                         |\n389\t| `Engine::truncate_wal()`         | `TruncateWalReport`      | `PRAGMA wal_checkpoint(TRUNCATE)` + report counters. Operator path in `design/recovery.md:153`. Low build risk.                                                                                                                                                           |\n390\t| `Engine::purge_logical_id(id)`   | `PurgeLogicalIdReport`   | Cascade scope spec'd 2026-05-12 in `design/recovery.md § Logical-id purge and restore`: canonical + `latest_state` + projection rows; `append_only_log` preserved as restore replay source. Standard build risk.                                                          |\n391\t| `Engine::restore_logical_id(id)` | `RestoreLogicalIdReport` | Replay source + semantics spec'd 2026-05-12 in `design/recovery.md § Logical-id purge and restore`: replays `append_only_log` history through the writer; typed failure modes (`NoRestorationSource`, `ConflictingActiveRow`, `IncompatibleSchema`). Standard build risk. |\n392\t\n393\tPrerequisite design landed 2026-05-12:\n394\t\n395\t- `design/engine.md § Canonical identity and supersession` defines\n396\t  `row_id` / `logical_id` / `superseded_at` and ID-generation policy.\n397\t- `design/recovery.md § Logical-id purge and restore` specifies\n398\t  cascade scope, replay source, and typed failure modes for the two\n399\t  logical-id verbs.\n400\t\n401\tSlice order:\n402\t\n403\t1. Build the five low-risk seams (`verify_embedder`, `dump_schema`,\n404\t   `dump_row_counts`, `dump_profile`, `truncate_wal`).\n405\t2. Build `purge_logical_id` per the spec'd cascade.\n406\t3. Build `restore_logical_id` per the spec'd replay semantics.\n407\t4. Extend facade re-exports + `dev/interfaces/rust.md` for each new report\n408\t   type.\n409\t5. Extend CLI wire-up + tests.\n410\t\n411\tFirst failing tests (10b):\n412\t\n413\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/tests/operator_cli.rs` extended to cover\n414\t  the remaining doctor verbs: `{AC-040a (verify-embedder, dump-schema,\n415\tdump-row-counts, dump-profile rows), AC-040b}`.\n416\t- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/tests/recovery_cli.rs` extended to cover\n417\t  `--truncate-wal`, `--purge-logical-id`, `--restore-logical-id`, including\n418\t  `AC-058` (full `recover --help` sub-flag enumeration).\n419\t\n420\tExit gate (10b):\n421\t\n422\t- All seven `doctor` verbs invocable with `--json`.\n423\t- All six `recover` sub-flags invocable with `--accept-data-loss` and\n424\t  refused without it.\n425\t- AC-040a / AC-040b / AC-058 fully satisfied (no partial / deferred rows).\n426\t\n427\t## Phase 11 — Bindings Parity and Packaging\n428\t\n429\tGoal: wire Python and TypeScript to the Rust engine and prove language parity."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e0d30c0-d2ee-4cef-baf2-390d4427d50f","uuid":"f9a46966-a199-4fc2-a5fb-c33bd4c862c0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T13:10:51.679Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-10b-B-purge-restore-20260516T131040Z/dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md","content":"10a commit range: `c7c51f1..12faeaf` (8 commits).\n\n### Phase 10b — Build remaining engine seams + complete CLI coverage\n\nEngine seams to build in 10b. Output shapes are already specified in\n`design/recovery.md` lines 73–77; this slice implements them and re-exports\nthe corresponding reporting types per the same facade rule.\n\n| Seam method                      | Output type              | Spec status / build risk                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |\n| -------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `Engine::verify_embedder(...)`   | `VerifyEmbedderReport`   | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:73`). Reads stored embedder identity (already persisted per AC-048/048b) + compares to supplied. Low build risk.                                                                                                                 |\n| `Engine::dump_schema()`          | `DumpSchemaReport`       | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:75`). SQLite introspection (`user_version`, `sqlite_schema` walk). Low build risk.                                                                                                                                               |\n| `Engine::dump_row_counts()`      | `DumpRowCountsReport`    | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:76`). Canonical table row counts. Low build risk.                                                                                                                                                                                |\n| `Engine::dump_profile()`         | `DumpProfileReport`      | Output shape locked (`design/recovery.md:77`). Reads stored embedder identity / vectorized kinds. Low build risk.                                                                                                                                                         |\n| `Engine::truncate_wal()`         | `TruncateWalReport`      | `PRAGMA wal_checkpoint(TRUNCATE)` + report counters. Operator path in `design/recovery.md:153`. Low build risk.                                                                                                                                                           |\n| `Engine::purge_logical_id(id)`   | `PurgeLogicalIdReport`   | Cascade scope spec'd 2026-05-12 in `design/recovery.md § Logical-id purge and restore`: canonical + `latest_state` + projection rows; `append_only_log` preserved as restore replay source. Standard build risk.                                                          |\n| `Engine::restore_logical_id(id)` | `RestoreLogicalIdReport` | Replay source + semantics spec'd 2026-05-12 in `design/recovery.md § Logical-id purge and restore`: replays `append_only_log` history through the writer; typed failure modes (`NoRestorationSource`, `ConflictingActiveRow`, `IncompatibleSchema`). Standard build risk. |\n\nPrerequisite design landed 2026-05-12:\n\n- `design/engine.md § Canonical identity and supersession` defines\n  `row_id` / `logical_id` / `superseded_at` and ID-generation policy.\n- `design/recovery.md § Logical-id purge and restore` specifies\n  cascade scope, replay source, and typed failure modes for the two\n  logical-id verbs.\n\nSlice order:\n\n1. Build the five low-risk seams (`verify_embedder`, `dump_schema`,\n   `dump_row_counts`, `dump_profile`, `truncate_wal`).\n2. Build `purge_logical_id` per the spec'd cascade.\n3. Build `restore_logical_id` per the spec'd replay semantics.\n4. Extend facade re-exports + `dev/interfaces/rust.md` for each new report\n   type.\n5. Extend CLI wire-up + tests.\n\nFirst failing tests (10b):\n\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/tests/operator_cli.rs` extended to cover\n  the remaining doctor verbs: `{AC-040a (verify-embedder, dump-schema,\ndump-row-counts, dump-profile rows), AC-040b}`.\n- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/tests/recovery_cli.rs` extended to cover\n  `--truncate-wal`, `--purge-logical-id`, `--restore-logical-id`, including\n  `AC-058` (full `recover --help` sub-flag enumeration).\n\nExit gate (10b):\n\n- All seven `doctor` verbs invocable with `--json`.\n- All six `recover` sub-flags invocable with `--accept-data-loss` and\n  refused without it.\n- AC-040a / AC-040b / AC-058 fully satisfied (no partial / deferred rows).\n\n## Phase 11 — Bindings Parity and Packaging\n\nGoal: wire Python and TypeScript to the Rust engine and prove language parity.","numLines":55,"startLine":375,"totalLines":625}}}
