{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GEQkSRZmht2Nj6u1kgVhMg","type":"tool_result","content":"90\tThese are CLI-only ergonomic types; they are NOT exposed as runtime SDK\n91\tverbs (recovery remains CLI-only — see Non-presence below).\n92\t\n93\tRe-exported types (canonical spellings, locked 2026-05-12; extended\n94\t2026-05-15):\n95\t\n96\t- `CheckIntegrityOpts`\n97\t- `IntegrityReport`\n98\t- `SafeExportArtifact`\n99\t- `TraceReport`\n100\t- `TraceEvent`\n101\t- `RebuildReport`\n102\t- `RebuildKind`\n103\t- `ExciseReport`\n104\t- `VerifyEmbedderReport`\n105\t- `VerifyEmbedderStatus`\n106\t- `DumpSchemaReport`\n107\t- `SchemaObject`\n108\t- `DumpRowCountsReport`\n109\t- `TableRowCount`\n110\t- `DumpProfileReport`\n111\t- `TruncateWalReport`\n112\t- `TruncateWalStatus`\n113\t\n114\tEngine methods backing these types are owned by `design/recovery.md` and\n115\tlisted in `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` (Phase 10a + Phase 10b-A).\n116\tAdditional recovery seam types added by Phase 10b-B (e.g.\n117\t`PurgeLogicalIdReport`, `RestoreLogicalIdReport`) land here as the\n118\tcorresponding engine seams are implemented, per the same re-export\n119\trule.\n120\t\n121\t## Non-presence\n122\t\n123\tThe Rust runtime surface does not expose recovery verbs. Recovery remains CLI\n124\tonly per `design/recovery.md` and `design/bindings.md`. The re-exported\n125\trecovery types above are present as compile-time symbols for `fathomdb-cli`;\n126\tthe runtime `Engine` does NOT gain corresponding SDK methods.\n127\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e0d30c0-d2ee-4cef-baf2-390d4427d50f","uuid":"2b16fe6a-9d22-437e-bb07-eda0906f3bc0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T13:10:53.173Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-10b-B-purge-restore-20260516T131040Z/dev/interfaces/rust.md","content":"These are CLI-only ergonomic types; they are NOT exposed as runtime SDK\nverbs (recovery remains CLI-only — see Non-presence below).\n\nRe-exported types (canonical spellings, locked 2026-05-12; extended\n2026-05-15):\n\n- `CheckIntegrityOpts`\n- `IntegrityReport`\n- `SafeExportArtifact`\n- `TraceReport`\n- `TraceEvent`\n- `RebuildReport`\n- `RebuildKind`\n- `ExciseReport`\n- `VerifyEmbedderReport`\n- `VerifyEmbedderStatus`\n- `DumpSchemaReport`\n- `SchemaObject`\n- `DumpRowCountsReport`\n- `TableRowCount`\n- `DumpProfileReport`\n- `TruncateWalReport`\n- `TruncateWalStatus`\n\nEngine methods backing these types are owned by `design/recovery.md` and\nlisted in `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` (Phase 10a + Phase 10b-A).\nAdditional recovery seam types added by Phase 10b-B (e.g.\n`PurgeLogicalIdReport`, `RestoreLogicalIdReport`) land here as the\ncorresponding engine seams are implemented, per the same re-export\nrule.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nThe Rust runtime surface does not expose recovery verbs. Recovery remains CLI\nonly per `design/recovery.md` and `design/bindings.md`. The re-exported\nrecovery types above are present as compile-time symbols for `fathomdb-cli`;\nthe runtime `Engine` does NOT gain corresponding SDK methods.\n","numLines":38,"startLine":90,"totalLines":127}}}
