{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SybnxGidKn3Xx2yTZJ8rPE","type":"tool_result","content":"60\t\n61\t## Recover root\n62\t\n63\t`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n64\t\n65\t```text\n66\tfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n67\t  [--truncate-wal]\n68\t  [--rebuild-vec0]\n69\t  [--rebuild-projections]\n70\t  [--excise-source <id>]\n71\t  [--purge-logical-id <id>]\n72\t  [--restore-logical-id <id>]\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\tExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n76\t\n77\t`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\n78\treject it as unknown.\n79\t\n80\t`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\n81\tor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\n82\tbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n83\t\n84\t## Error to exit-code mapping"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e0d30c0-d2ee-4cef-baf2-390d4427d50f","uuid":"6734de99-4873-47f1-b5fa-8dcbc8461a5c","timestamp":"2026-05-16T13:10:54.962Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-10b-B-purge-restore-20260516T131040Z/dev/interfaces/cli.md","content":"\n## Recover root\n\n`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n\n```text\nfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n  [--truncate-wal]\n  [--rebuild-vec0]\n  [--rebuild-projections]\n  [--excise-source <id>]\n  [--purge-logical-id <id>]\n  [--restore-logical-id <id>]\n```\n\nExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n\n`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\nreject it as unknown.\n\n`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\nor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\nbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n\n## Error to exit-code mapping","numLines":25,"startLine":60,"totalLines":129}}}
